From: Ilia Alshanetsky <ilia@ilia.ws>
Date: $(date +%Y-%m-%d)
Subject: [PATCH 3/5] client: pass full Query to SendQuery in BeginInsert (preserve query_id)

`Client::Impl::BeginInsert(Query query)` was calling `SendQuery(query.GetText())`.

The string constructor gives an empty default query id, so any id the caller supplied (via the two-argument form or by building a Query with settings/params) was lost. The INSERT would appear in `system.query_log` with an auto-generated id.

The one-shot `Insert()` path was unaffected because it already passed the full Query object.

Fix is a one-line change to preserve the caller's Query object.

---
 clickhouse/client.cpp | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/clickhouse/client.cpp b/clickhouse/client.cpp
index 8e8e0f0..e0e0e0e 100644
--- a/clickhouse/client.cpp
+++ b/clickhouse/client.cpp
@@ -546,7 +546,7 @@ Block Client::Impl::BeginInsert(Query query) {
         return true;
     });

-    SendQuery(query.GetText());
+    SendQuery(query);

     // Wait for a data packet and return
     uint64_t server_packet = 0;
